## Computed Values

#### dol_avg_monthly_income

DOL quarterly earnings divided by 3 to get average monthly income for comparison

*Source: 523B — Reasonable Compatibility*

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  definition dol_avg_monthly_income equals
    d_o_l_record.dol_quarterly_earnings / 3

```

#### is_compatible

True when DOL-adjusted income is within 10% of client-adjusted income (reasonably compatible per 523B)

*Source: 523B — Reasonable Compatibility*

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  definition is_compatible equals
    (if dol_result.adjusted_earned_income - client_result.adjusted_earned_income >= $0 then dol_result.adjusted_earned_income - client_result.adjusted_earned_income else $0 - (dol_result.adjusted_earned_income - client_result.adjusted_earned_income)) <= client_result.adjusted_earned_income * 0.10

```

#### manual_verification_required

True when manual verification is needed: either DOL data is unavailable (action 5), or client is within limit but DOL is above and NOT reasonably compatible (action 4 incompatible path)

*Source: 523B — Reasonable Compatibility actions 4 and 5*

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  rule manual_verification_required under condition true
    consequence not fulfilled

scope EligibilityDecision:
  exception
  rule manual_verification_required
    under condition
      not d_o_l_record.dol_earned_income_available or (client_result.adjusted_earned_income <= income_limit and
      dol_result.adjusted_earned_income > income_limit and
      not is_compatible)
    consequence fulfilled

```

## Rules

#### AK-ELIG-DENY-001

Deny when both client-stated and DOL-verified adjusted income exceed the income standard (523B action 2 — no compatibility check needed)

*Source: 523B — Reasonable Compatibility action 2*

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  rule deny_rule_1_triggered under condition true
    consequence not fulfilled

scope EligibilityDecision:
  exception
  rule deny_rule_1_triggered
    under condition
      d_o_l_record.dol_earned_income_available and
      client_result.adjusted_earned_income > income_limit and
      dol_result.adjusted_earned_income > income_limit
    consequence fulfilled

```

#### AK-ELIG-DENY-002

Deny when client-stated income exceeds the standard but DOL income is at or below — accept client statement and deny without compatibility check (523B action 3)

*Source: 523B — Reasonable Compatibility action 3*

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  rule deny_rule_2_triggered under condition true
    consequence not fulfilled

scope EligibilityDecision:
  exception
  rule deny_rule_2_triggered
    under condition
      d_o_l_record.dol_earned_income_available and
      client_result.adjusted_earned_income > income_limit and
      dol_result.adjusted_earned_income <= income_limit
    consequence fulfilled

```

## Decision

#### eligible

Medicaid income eligibility result: approve if adjusted income at or below income standard; deny if above standard and not compatible with DOL; manual_verification if above standard but DOL income is compatible

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  definition eligible equals
    if (number of reasons) > 0 then Deny
    else if manual_verification_required then ManualVerification else Approve

```

```catala
scope EligibilityDecision:
  definition all_reason_entries equals
    [ ReasonEntry { -- triggered: deny_rule_1_triggered -- code: IncomeExceedsStandardBoth }
    ; ReasonEntry { -- triggered: deny_rule_2_triggered -- code: IncomeExceedsStandardClientOnly }
    ]

scope EligibilityDecision:
  definition reasons equals
    map each entry among
      (list of e among all_reason_entries such that e.triggered)
    to entry.code

```

